class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

Explanation
We use lastCnt and lastGroupMax to store the previous group information and curGroupMax to store the current group information. In the loop, if the current number of set bits is equal to the number of set bits of the previous number, then we can continue to compare with the largest number of the previous group to ensure that the number can continue to be swapped to the right. Otherwise, if the number of set bits of the current number is not equal to the number of set bits of the previous number, we should start a new group. We should also record the maximum number of the previous group in lastGroupMax.

